Subject:    IETF Domain Working Group agenda?
From:       <a href="?a=95837816800007&r=1&w=2">"Philip Almquist" &lt;almquist () jessica ! stanford ! edu&gt;</a>
Date:       <a href="?l=namedroppers&r=1&w=2&b=199011">1990-11-01 19:23:12</a></font>
[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837798827083&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837798827083&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

	I am at least tentatively planning on holding a meeting of the
DNS Working Group at the Boulder IETF meeting, and am soliciting
opinions about what ought to be included on the agenda.

	Is domain name service in the Internet a solved problem :~), or
are there things we need to (and/or want to) work on?  This will
probably be a half-day meeting.
						Philip

PS: As a possible starting point, I have enumerated below the projects
    that are currently listed in the group's charter:

      -  Adding load balancing capability to the DNS.
      -  Adding DNS variables to the MIB.
      -  Implementation catalog for DNS software.
      -  Responsible Person Record.
      -  Adding network naming capability to the DNS.
      -  Evaluate short-term measures to improve, or at least
	 describe the security of the DNS.

    A few other issues that have been posed on various mailing lists
    recently include:

      - What do the ISDN RR types really mean?
      - Should domaind have A records?
      - Should there be a DECNET QCLASS?
      - Compression in new RR types?
      - (Yet another round of) bogus servers for "." and "*".

